1984, and
later earned a Ph.D. in military
history.

02:06.193 --> 02:11.264 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
His doctoral thesis, about the
failures of
military and political
leadership during the

02:11.298 --> 02:17.237 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Vietnam War, later became a
well-regarded
book titled "Dereliction of
Duty."

02:17.270 --> 02:23.243 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
During the first Gulf War with
Iraq in 1991,
he lead a tank unit that
prevailed against

02:23.276 --> 02:25.946 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Iraq's powerful Republican
Guard.

02:25.979 --> 02:32.519 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He also lead American forces in
Iraq in 2005,
and successfully brought
stability to a city

02:32.552 --> 02:35.622 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that had been rife with ethnic
conflict.

02:35.655 --> 02:38.892 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For more on all of this, we turn
to Washington
Post reporter Greg Jaffe.

02:38.925 --> 02:41.728 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
