have known him,
what, for 14 years?

02:45.499 --> 02:47.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GREG JAFFE, The Washington Post:
Yes, I think
2002.

02:47.134 --> 02:49.002 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: 2002.

02:49.036 --> 02:50.137 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What should we know about him?

02:50.170 --> 02:52.773 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GREG JAFFE: He's fiercely
opinionated.

02:52.806 --> 02:54.174 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He's very, very smart.

02:54.207 --> 02:55.175 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
He's passionate.

02:55.208 --> 02:56.877 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
He's funny.

02:56.910 --> 03:02.315 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He understands the media, I
think, and talks
to reporters, interestingly.

03:02.349 --> 03:04.317 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I don't think he views them as
the enemy.

03:04.351 --> 03:09.656 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, you know, I think the one
knock against
him is, when he believes he's
right, he passionately

03:09.689 --> 03:12.759 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
argues that point and he doesn't
stop.

03:12.793 --> 03:14.961 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think, after a while, that
can be too
much for folks.

03:14.995 --> 03:17.297 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Tell me about his
military
career.

03:17.330 --> 03:24.304 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We were just reporting he had a
very successful
career during the first Iraq --
the Gulf War.

03:24.337 --> 03:26.239 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What made him so successful?

03:26.273 --> 03:30.977 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GREG JAFFE: Well, during the
first Gulf War,
he was involved in the Battle of
73 Easting

03:31.011 --> 03:31.978 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
there.

03:32.012 --> 03:34.047 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And so he was a tank company
commander.

03:34.081 --> 03:40.554 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And his tank company prevailed
against a much
larger unit of the Iraqi
Republican Guard.

03:40.587 --> 03:43.457 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
His real fame, though, came
later in Iraq
in 2006.

03:43.490 --> 03:46.460 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And what made him
so successful?

03:46.493 --> 03:50.464 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GREG JAFFE: You know, he was his
group, I
think "The New Yorker" described
them as -- his

03:50.497 --> 03:55.635 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
unit in Iraq as rebels against
an incoherent
strategy was a great line from
"The New Yorker."

03:55.669 --> 03:59.439 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And at that time, the strategy
in the U.S.
was, we will stand -- the U.S.
strategy in

03:59.473 --> 04:02.776 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Iraq was, we will stand down as
the Iraqis
stand up.

04:02.809 --> 04:04.945 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It was training the Iraqi
forces.

04:04.978 --> 04:09.182 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He went against that and said,
look, we can't
train the Iraqi forms until we
stabilize the

04:09.216 --> 04:10.951 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
situation.

04:10.984 --> 04:15.422 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So he pushed his troops into the
city of Tal
Afar, established 29 outposts in
the city,

04:15.455 --> 04:18.959 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
