34:19.624 --> 34:27.599 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: India's capital,
Delhi, now
outranks Beijing as the world's
most polluted

34:27.632 --> 34:28.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
large metropolis.

34:28.767 --> 34:31.436 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And it's taking a toll on its
resident's health.

34:31.469 --> 34:35.674 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, as special correspondent
Fred de Sam
Lazaro reports, there are
efforts under way

34:35.707 --> 34:38.276 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to make the city's air less
toxic.

34:38.310 --> 34:41.813 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's part of his ongoing series
Agents for
Change.

34:41.846 --> 34:49.821 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: He murmurs
and he gasps,
waiting for a spot to free up,
for a chance

34:49.854 --> 34:53.158 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to just breathe.

34:53.191 --> 34:58.129 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As nebulizer treatments open up
the lungs
of a handful of patients, dozens
more await

34:58.163 --> 35:02.834 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
their turn at the chest clinic
in a Delhi
government hospital.

35:02.867 --> 35:05.103 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is the scene outside of the
doctor's
office.

35:05.136 --> 35:07.272 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Clinic hours are 9:00 in the
morning until
1:00.

35:07.305 --> 35:13.011 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And on a typical day, the doctor
says he sees
about 120 patients who've been
here before

35:13.044 --> 35:16.982 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and 30 brand-new ones.

35:17.015 --> 35:22.120 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Three to four patients are seen
at the same
time, in the same room, by Dr.
Raj Kumar and

35:22.153 --> 35:25.090 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
his team of junior doctors and
residents.

35:25.123 --> 35:26.992 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The most common complaint?

35:27.025 --> 35:32.530 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Simply change of season, the
winter, which
brings dust and tiny carbon
particulates into

35:32.564 --> 35:33.531 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the environment

35:33.565 --> 35:35.333 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

35:35.367 --> 35:37.335 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RAJ KUMAR, India: When there is
a change in
environment or increase in the
particulate

35:37.369 --> 35:43.708 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
matter and everything, these
asthmatic and
COPD patients do get
exacerbation of their

35:43.742 --> 35:45.010 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
symptoms.

35:45.043 --> 35:46.077 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: They get
exacerbation
of their symptoms?

35:46.111 --> 35:47.078 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

35:47.112 --> 35:48.947 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
RAJ KUMAR: Yes.

35:48.980 --> 35:51.850 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Dr. Kumar
can do little
more than check on their
medications and advise

35:51.883 --> 35:58.289 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
patients to avoid some of the
most polluted
outdoor air on the planet.

35:58.323 --> 36:05.797 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Weather and wind patterns are
blamed for trapping
pollutants over India's capital,
carbon dioxide,

36:05.830 --> 36:08.066 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ozone and fine carbon particles.

36:08.099 --> 36:12.337 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Dirty fuels are the culprit from
several sources.

36:12.370 --> 36:17.675 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Automobiles are the major one.

36:17.709 --> 36:22.847 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On average, 1,400 new vehicles
are added to
Delhi's streets every day, most
now burning

36:22.881 --> 36:28.586 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a highly polluting diesel long
outlawed in
Europe and the United States.

36:28.620 --> 36:34.659 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
By 2021, diesel fuel here will
meet European
standards.

36:34.692 --> 36:40.465 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The government has also promised
to shut down
old coal-fired plants and
restrict new ones.

36:40.498 --> 36:45.870 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And wood- and coal-burning brick
kilns has
been moved farther away from the
city.

36:45.904 --> 36:50.408 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But the pollution continues.

36:50.442 --> 36:55.547 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
To get an idea of how polluted
the air is,
we went to one of the cleanest
places in Delhi,

36:55.580 --> 36:57.849 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the American Embassy School.

36:57.882 --> 37:02.353 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It serves the children of
American and other
expats and diplomats.

37:02.387 --> 37:07.292 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Many don face masks, but only
until they're
inside, says the director, Ellen
Stern.

37:07.325 --> 37:10.128 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ELLEN STERN, Director, American
Embassy School:
We have an air system that goes
all the way

37:10.161 --> 37:11.930 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
through the school.

37:11.963 --> 37:17.502 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We now have four different kinds
of filters
on it that filter out various
kinds of things.

37:17.535 --> 37:26.111 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Barun
Aggarwal showed
me the elaborate system his
company, BreatheEasy,

37:26.144 --> 37:31.149 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
has set up in the school,
pulling out the
first layer of filter, thickly
coated with

37:31.182 --> 37:32.817 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
a grimy soot.

37:32.851 --> 37:38.356 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, if you were to walk outside
today, this
is what is coming into your
lungs?

37:38.389 --> 37:40.091 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BARUN AGGARWAL, BreatheEasy:
Absolutely.

37:40.125 --> 37:42.994 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Most of the black carbon
actually passes through
a filter like this.

37:43.027 --> 37:44.429 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
This is mostly dust.

37:44.462 --> 37:46.998 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the black carbon will get
trapped in the
finer particle filters.

37:47.031 --> 37:49.767 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: So, how old
is this accumulation?

37:49.801 --> 37:54.038 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BARUN AGGARWAL: Less than six
days.

37:54.072 --> 37:59.144 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: The fine
particle filters
also show stark before-and-after
evidence

37:59.177 --> 38:00.979 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of the harmful air outside.

38:01.012 --> 38:06.284 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You would think such systems
would be in strong
demand, but Aggarwal says, aside
from a few

38:06.317 --> 38:11.089 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
buildings mostly occupied by
expats, its been
a hard sell.

38:11.122 --> 38:15.894 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Among India's growing middle
class, he says,
he's there's denial or
indifference, a sense

38:15.927 --> 38:19.831 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
