India's rapid
economic progress.

38:19.864 --> 38:23.868 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARUN AGGARWAL: The number of
myths that are
there with regards to air
pollution in India

38:23.902 --> 38:25.637 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
are incredible.

38:25.670 --> 38:31.142 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The first one that I get by
mostly Indians
is that, if I breathe clean air
for eight

38:31.176 --> 38:35.180 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
hours, then my immunity will
come down, and
when I go out, I will fall sick.

38:35.213 --> 38:38.149 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Completely wrong, because this
is -- if you
believe that, then you should be
giving your

38:38.183 --> 38:40.185 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
children two packets of
cigarettes to smoke
every day.

38:40.218 --> 38:45.857 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: The problem,
like cigarette
smoking is, except for those
with lung disease,

38:45.890 --> 38:50.328 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the health consequences of
pollution, such
as lung and heart disease and
stroke, come

38:50.361 --> 38:51.829 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
later in life.

38:51.863 --> 38:53.765 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAMAL MEATTLE, Environmental
Activist: It'll
happen in 10, 20, 30 years.

38:53.798 --> 38:58.303 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So if you ask a 20-year-old, is
this important,
they say, no, no, no, forget it.

38:58.336 --> 38:59.304 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I have to make money.

38:59.337 --> 39:01.339 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I have to get ahead in life.

39:01.372 --> 39:04.976 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Kamal
Meattle is an environmental
activist who also designed the
embassy school's

39:05.009 --> 39:06.778 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
filtration system.

39:06.811 --> 39:12.150 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It works well, he says, but it
is no panacea
for a city of 20-plus million
residents.

39:12.183 --> 39:17.288 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAMAL MEATTLE: You cannot have
just air purifiers
and cleaning systems for the
people who can

39:17.322 --> 39:18.923 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
afford them.

39:18.957 --> 39:23.094 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It has to be for the people who
are on the
road, who are in (INAUDIBLE)
slums.

39:23.127 --> 39:28.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And they have to be dealing with
people who
go on motorcycles, go on metros,
go on buses.

39:28.099 --> 39:31.169 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They're the ones who are exposed
most to the
pollution.

39:31.202 --> 39:35.940 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Meattle, who
trained at
MIT, has developed lower-cost
ways to cope

39:35.974 --> 39:40.979 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with the pollution, which we
measured just
outside an office building he
owns in central

39:41.012 --> 39:45.016 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Delhi, using an instrument used
to measure
fine carbon particles.

39:45.049 --> 39:46.551 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
KAMAL MEATTLE: Two-ninety, 288.

39:46.584 --> 39:49.153 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: What is the
WHO standard?

39:49.187 --> 39:50.421 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
KAMAL MEATTLE: It's 50.

39:50.455 --> 39:53.524 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: So, what you
have outside
your building...

39:53.558 --> 39:55.360 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
KAMAL MEATTLE: Six times.

39:55.393 --> 39:59.564 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: ... is an
air quality
that's six times worse than the
WHO standard?

39:59.597 --> 40:00.565 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
KAMAL MEATTLE: That's right.

40:00.598 --> 40:02.100 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
That's right.

40:02.133 --> 40:03.901 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Can we step
back inside
and see what it's like inside?

40:03.935 --> 40:11.175 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
From 290, the level dropped to
nine, thanks
not just to filters and air
purifiers, but

40:11.209 --> 40:15.546 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to plants, thousands of them in
this rooftop
greenhouse.

40:15.580 --> 40:22.620 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But this greenhouse produces
clean air, and
each floor is pulling it in as
needed.

40:22.654 --> 40:23.621 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
KAMAL MEATTLE: Yes.

40:23.655 --> 40:26.724 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And there are plants on each
floor also.

40:26.758 --> 40:31.462 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is the central air cleaning
system for
the whole building.

40:31.496 --> 40:34.699 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Plants do
more than produce
oxygen, he says.

40:34.732 --> 40:37.368 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They are natural air purifiers.

40:37.402 --> 40:42.940 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Their roots eat bacteria and
fungi and they
absorb chemicals like
formaldehyde and benzene

40:42.974 --> 40:44.776 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
produced by office products.

40:44.809 --> 40:48.913 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAMAL MEATTLE: These are areca
palms for the
day time, bamboo palm.

40:48.946 --> 40:53.351 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Most
importantly, he says,
these are common, fast-growing
species and

40:53.384 --> 40:58.022 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
should be in every home for
clean air benefits
to both lungs and brains.

40:58.056 --> 41:03.294 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAMAL MEATTLE: Harvard and also
University
of California at Berkeley have
done studies

41:03.328 --> 41:08.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to show that your cognitive
abilities improve
in such an environment.

41:08.099 --> 41:12.770 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: They're
small steps people
can take indoors, but he
acknowledges there's

41:12.804 --> 41:18.776 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a huge complex problem outside
these clean
air bubbles, not easily solved
in India's

41:18.810 --> 41:20.645 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
chaotic democracy.

41:20.678 --> 41:25.550 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAMAL MEATTLE: I think its
politicians anywhere
in the world, they think the
same, that they

41:25.583 --> 41:30.321 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
will only act when they have
learned a solution
and it's a very straightforward
solution.

41:30.355 --> 41:32.657 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Then they will implement it and
take credit
for it.

41:32.690 --> 41:38.096 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But until they find that they
don't -- or
they know that they don't have a
clean, straight

41:38.129 --> 41:40.031 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
solution, they will keep the
matter confused.

41:40.064 --> 41:44.202 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: But
environmentalists
say years of lobbying seem to be
yielding

41:44.235 --> 41:49.807 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
some results, helped by prodding
from India's
Supreme Court, which has
compelled government

41:49.841 --> 41:51.709 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
agencies to act.

41:51.743 --> 41:56.748 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One group claiming the credit
says it distributed
pollution gauges to prominent
Delhiites.

41:56.781 --> 42:01.719 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Its leader, Sunita Narain, says
campaign targets
included the court.

42:01.753 --> 42:03.688 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SUNITA NARAIN, Activist: We took
the machine
in.

42:03.721 --> 42:05.089 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We put the machine there.

42:05.123 --> 42:09.260 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And the chief justice said, this
is unacceptable.

42:09.293 --> 42:16.701 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So I think, slowly, that sense
of unacceptable,
this is not right, this is not
fair, it's

42:16.734 --> 42:21.539 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
increasing the burden of health
on our children,
we have to change it, that's
happened.

42:21.572 --> 42:26.511 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: But, in the
meantime,
for years to come, India's
capital and, for

42:26.544 --> 42:31.315 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that matter, most of its major
cities will
continue to be among the most
difficult places

42:31.349 --> 42:33.551 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
on Earth to breathe.

42:33.584 --> 42:37.655 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," this is
Fred de Sam
Lazaro in New Delhi.

42:37.688 --> 42:42.393 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Fred's reporting
