42:55.239 --> 42:57.842 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The Oscars are this coming
Sunday.

42:57.875 --> 43:02.580 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
One of the best picture
favorites is a coming-of-age
story that's been honored for
its approach

43:02.613 --> 43:05.950 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to dealing with sexual identity
and race.

43:05.983 --> 43:11.088 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
"Moonlight" grabbed its latest
award last
night: best screenplay from the
Writers Guild

43:11.122 --> 43:12.290 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of America.

43:12.323 --> 43:14.592 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's up for eight Oscars.

43:14.625 --> 43:17.528 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Jeffrey Brown sat down with the
filmmakers
this fall.

43:17.562 --> 43:22.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Here's a second look for our
series Beyond
the Red Carpet.

43:22.066 --> 43:31.843 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: It's a life we
don't often
see portrayed in commercial
films, a coming-of-age

43:31.876 --> 43:38.015 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
tale of love and anguish, a
movie that's garnered
critical acclaim for the story
it tells and

43:38.049 --> 43:40.418 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the beauty and power of its
telling.

43:40.451 --> 43:48.259 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In "Moonlight," we watch Chiron
growing up
in the Liberty City neighborhood
of Miami

43:48.292 --> 43:50.828 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
as the crack epidemic is taking
hold in the
1980s.

43:50.862 --> 44:01.672 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He is young, poor, black, and
coming to terms
with being gay, quietly and
painfully wrestling

44:01.706 --> 44:03.641 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
with these identities.

44:03.674 --> 44:09.447 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The story is based on the life
of Tarell Alvin
McCraney, who first wrote it as
a play and

44:09.480 --> 44:12.383 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
then the screenplay for the new
film.

44:12.416 --> 44:16.087 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
TARELL ALVIN MCCRANEY,
Screenwriter, "Moonlight":
It's a story that I still feel
like I have

44:16.120 --> 44:18.623 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to tell, but also that I have to
explore and
to understand.

44:18.656 --> 44:25.496 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, it's a story rooted in
events in my
own life that I'm trying to make
sense of

44:25.530 --> 44:28.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and make sense of the world out
of.

44:28.399 --> 44:33.037 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think, for me, I always am
interested
in trying to get a group of
people to have

44:33.070 --> 44:34.739 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the same conversation.

44:34.772 --> 44:36.707 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
BARRY JENKINS, Director,
"Moonlight": So,
Tarell and I grew up blocks from
one another.

44:36.741 --> 44:41.979 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Director Barry
Jenkins, who
also grew up poor in Liberty
City at the same

44:42.013 --> 44:47.051 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
time, and with a mother fighting
addiction,
presents the story in three
separate acts,

44:47.084 --> 44:50.288 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
using three different actors to
play Chiron.

44:50.321 --> 44:56.060 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At the new Museum of African
American History
and Culture, where the film was
recently screened,

44:56.093 --> 44:59.630 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
he told me he purposely kept the
actors from
watching one another.

44:59.664 --> 45:04.035 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARRY JENKINS: One of the themes
of the film
for me is about the way society
is shaping

45:04.068 --> 45:08.406 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
these young men from our
communities, through
positive reinforcement, negative
reinforcement.

45:08.439 --> 45:09.740 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
This is what masculinity looks
like.

45:09.774 --> 45:11.509 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
This is what it sounds like.

45:11.542 --> 45:14.712 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so much time passes between
each story
that I feel like the world has
shaped this

45:14.745 --> 45:16.714 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
character into a different
person.

45:16.747 --> 45:21.485 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I wanted to cast different
people to play
the same person, and I wanted
them to be different.

45:21.519 --> 45:26.223 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: We watch Chiron
grow through
high school, tormented by
bullies and his

45:26.257 --> 45:31.963 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
own insecurities, living with a
mother, played
by Naomie Harris, who sinks more
and more

45:31.996 --> 45:33.030 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
into addiction.

45:33.064 --> 45:37.001 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
NAOMIE HARRIS, Actress: What's
wrong?

45:37.034 --> 45:38.836 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
ACTOR: Nothing.

45:38.869 --> 45:44.709 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: This is a young
man who speaks
more loudly in his looks and
silences than

45:44.742 --> 45:46.377 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in words.

45:46.410 --> 45:48.779 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARRY JENKINS: The power of
cinema is that
we get to watch people, you
know?

45:48.813 --> 45:51.449 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we get to watch people,
like, in close-up.

45:51.482 --> 45:56.320 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so, if there's a scene on
the stage, the
audience can't get right in an
actor's eyes.

45:56.354 --> 45:58.189 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
But in cinema, they can.

45:58.222 --> 46:01.726 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think, because of that,
because of the
power of the feeling in a
person's eyes, you

46:01.759 --> 46:03.461 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
know, they can be doing --
active.

46:03.494 --> 46:06.397 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They can be less active, and yet
revealing
so much more.

46:06.430 --> 46:08.165 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think of "Moonlight," it's
like an iceberg
film.

46:08.199 --> 46:12.269 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You know the Hemingway phrase,
you know, 10
percent is above water, and 90
percent is

46:12.303 --> 46:13.270 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
below?

46:13.304 --> 46:15.106 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We flip it upside-down.

46:15.139 --> 46:18.009 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You know, we want to show you
that 90 percent
below water, but it's moving
very, very slow.

46:18.042 --> 46:19.877 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You know, it's a patient film.

46:19.910 --> 46:23.614 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But the character is revealing
himself by
these terms and his expressions.

46:23.648 --> 46:27.685 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TREVANTE RHODES, Actor: What you
looking at
me like that for?

46:27.718 --> 46:28.819 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ACTOR: What, man?

46:28.853 --> 46:31.956 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Come on, you just drove down
here?

46:31.989 --> 46:34.892 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
TREVANTE RHODES: Yes.

46:34.925 --> 46:41.399 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: The adult Chiron
is played
by Trevante Rhodes, a one-time
track and field

46:41.432 --> 46:46.671 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
star at the University of Texas
who only found
his way into acting his senior
year.

46:46.704 --> 46:51.509 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TREVANTE RHODES: I think the
beauty of that
scene was Chiron, he didn't
know.

46:51.542 --> 46:56.514 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: An outgoing and
gregarious
man, he told me how he
approached playing

46:56.547 --> 46:58.315 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a character so different.

46:58.349 --> 47:02.953 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TREVANTE RHODES: So, for me, it
was really
just about walking around L.A.
with the three

47:02.987 --> 47:08.092 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
weeks I had prior to filming
feeling as if
-- feeling as if I had a secret
to hide from

47:08.125 --> 47:09.660 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
everyone?

47:09.694 --> 47:11.462 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: You were walking
around feeling
and getting into the character.

47:11.495 --> 47:12.863 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TREVANTE RHODES: Walking around
L.A., getting
in the character, walking
around, feeling

47:12.897 --> 47:17.568 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
as if I had this secret, feeling
as if I connected
with someone.

47:17.601 --> 47:19.136 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They would be able to see
through me.

47:19.170 --> 47:20.504 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They would be able to see my
insecurities.

47:20.538 --> 47:22.540 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They would be able to see this
mask that I
was putting up.

47:22.573 --> 47:26.711 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They would be able to see all of
these things,
