myself, because
Chiron had this self-hate.

47:31.048 --> 47:32.817 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And because of that, he couldn't
love others.

47:32.850 --> 47:38.355 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I feel that all of us really
relate to
Chiron in the sense that we all,
at some point,

47:38.389 --> 47:41.559 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are insecure about something in
our life,
you know?

47:41.592 --> 47:48.632 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I'm someone who I try to
make sense of
everything, and I feel like
Chiron tends to

47:48.666 --> 47:50.568 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
do the same thing, just in a
different way.

47:50.601 --> 47:52.036 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The context is a bit different.

47:52.069 --> 47:53.804 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
NAOMIE HARRIS: And who is you?

47:53.838 --> 47:55.606 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MAHERSHALA ALI, Actor: Nobody.

47:55.639 --> 48:00.478 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Another
compelling character
is Juan, played by Mahershala
Ali, a drug

48:00.511 --> 48:03.681 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
dealer stepping in as a father
figure to the
