co-anchor, Jim

50:13.143 --> 50:15.813 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Lehrer, anything to do with
buses.

50:15.846 --> 50:21.919 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But one Virginia man owns dozens
of giant
sculptures of our nation's
commanders in chief.

50:21.952 --> 50:26.690 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
To mark President's Day, the
"NewsHour"'s
Julia Griffin has paid his
collection a visit.

50:26.724 --> 50:33.664 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JULIA GRIFFIN: Cracked and
crumbling, battered
and broken, these are the faces
of Presidents

50:33.697 --> 50:35.332 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Park.

50:35.366 --> 50:41.238 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The 10-acre tourist destination
outside of
Colonial Williamsburg opened in
2004.

50:41.272 --> 50:42.940 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
The main attraction?

50:42.973 --> 50:49.246 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Forty-three Texas-sized busts of
presidents
past by Houston artist David
Adickes.

50:49.280 --> 50:53.284 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Utility contractor Howard
Hankins helped build
the original park.

50:53.317 --> 50:56.687 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HOWARD HANKINS, Utility
Contractor: The eyes
look like they're staring at
you, just gazing

50:56.720 --> 50:57.688 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
